 We will extend our analysis to include the evolution of quantum correlations
 of second order, in particular we consider the quantum evolution equation
 of the form:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\partial_{t}\left\langle \hat{\sigma}_{i}^{\alpha}\hat{\sigma}_{j}^{\beta}\right\rangle  & ={\rm Tr}\left(\hat{\sigma}_{i}^{\alpha}\hat{\sigma}_{j}^{\beta}\partial_{t}\hat{\rho}\right).
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
with 
\begin_inset Formula $i\neq j$
\end_inset

.
